The Alex Jones Show 
Sunday, 20 December 2009

audio files are divided on half-hour breaks
[sebaygo1]




The 2 hour Sunday show is typically a review of the past week's news and a look forward to the coming week's events.


Alex takes a number of calls and in the second hour spends a fair amount of time laying out his position on the creation vs. evolution debate.


Other topics include the partial victory in Copenhagen and the likely defeat coming on the health insurance reform bill.  Alex also tags the new movie "Avatar" as total propaganda.
